# Project General (XForge)

Domain rules override generic habits. This repo is **TypeScript + pnpm + Turborepo** ŌĆö not JavaScript, Bun, or npm-by-default.

## Source of truth (read order)

1. User instruction in the current message
2. `AGENTS.md` and `skills/reference/*.md` (architecture, Vercel deployment, Next.js MCP)
3. `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` for the files you touch
4. Next.js APIs: MCP `nextjs_docs` from `nextjs-docs://llms-index` ŌĆö training data is stale (`/docs/app/guides/ai-agents`)

## Working defaults

- Smallest correct diff; match existing package patterns
- Advice or yes/no ŌåÆ **answer in prose first**, then code (`agent-discipline.mdc`)
- Ship complete changes ŌĆö no TODO placeholders unless the feature is explicitly scaffold-only
- Names: kebab-case files; PascalCase components; camelCase functions/variables
- Uncertain ŌåÆ say so; read the codebase or docs ŌĆö do not invent APIs

## Tooling

```bash
pnpm --filter <package> typecheck   # narrow gate first
pnpm --filter <package> test
pnpm lint:biome
pnpm lint:architecture              # when boundaries matter
```

Use **pnpm** only unless the user specifies otherwise. Biome for format/lint ŌĆö not ESLint/Prettier for new work.

## Dev / build policy

Do **not** start `dev`, `build`, or other long-running servers unless the user asks ŌĆö avoids port conflicts with an existing dev session.

Runtime checks when appropriate: MCP `nextjs_index` ŌåÆ `nextjs_call` `get_errors` ŌĆö see `nextjs-mcp-quality.mdc`.

## Hooks (enforced ŌĆö see `.cursor/hooks.json`)

| Rule concern | Hook | Event |
|--------------|------|-------|
| No destructive git on WIP | `block-destructive-git.mjs` | `beforeShellExecution` |
| No dev/start unless asked | `block-dev-servers.mjs` | `beforeShellExecution` |
| pnpm monorepo | `warn-wrong-package-manager.mjs` | `beforeShellExecution` |
| Workspace compose human-owned | `guard-workspace-compose.mjs` | `preToolUse` |
| NEXT_PUBLIC_ secrets | `guard-next-public-env.mjs` | `preToolUse` |
| Vercel prod deploy | `ask-vercel-production.mjs` | `beforeShellExecution` |
| Vercel MCP deploy | `guard-vercel-deploy-mcp.mjs` | `beforeMCPExecution` |
| vercel env pull | `ask-vercel-env-pull.mjs` | `beforeShellExecution` |
| App/storybook/metadata-ui gates | `stop-quality-gates.mjs` | `stop` (self-heal ├Ś3) |

Everything else stays in rules (answer-first, execution pipeline, UI patterns) ŌĆö not hookable deterministically.

